<p>Note that we have added an <code class="highlighter-rouge">auth</code> fixture to each test function to compute the
access tokens and geneate the token headers for accessing each endpoint. The
token header is then passed to each request using the <code class="highlighter-rouge">headers</code> key.</p>

<p>Appropriate error responses should be generated for the cases where the token
header is either invalid or missing.</p>

<p>The update to the <code class="highlighter-rouge">auth</code> fixture in the <code class="highlighter-rouge">conftest</code> module is shown below.</p>

<div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>
<span class="c1"># tests.v1.conftest
</span>
<span class="c1"># ... previous code
</span>
<span class="k">class</span> <span class="nc">AuthActions</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">object</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="s">"""
    This class provides methods for authenticating users.
